FarmBills2020 paves the way for the creation of One India, One Agriculture Market. It enables farmers to get the best prices for their produce and ensure better income for farmers

#FarmBills2020
FarmBills2020 does not intend to phase out Minimum Support Price (MSP). On the contrary, it gives farmers more choices and avenues to sell, enabling them to get better prices for their produce.

#FarmBills2020
Barriers on selling agricultural produce forced farmers to sell at low prices even during times of surplus in mandis. Farm Bills 2020 empowers farmers to sell to other regions of India at higher prices enabling farmers to get better returns

#FarmBills2020
FarmBills2020 has brought in a legal framework to enable farmers to partner with food processors and exporters. This will enable farmers to get access to modernized farming practices, assured returns, and sell high-value agricultural produce

#FarmBills2020
FarmBills2020 has enabled farmers to carry out barrier-free inter-state trade and e-trading. This has freed them from the clutches of Middlemen and exploiting cartels, heralding a new era of prosperity for farmers.
